      • getPlugins

        @Nonnull
List<Plugin> getPlugins()
        Returns all registered plugins ordered by their priority.
        Returns:

      • getPlugins

        @Nonnull
<T extends Plugin> List<T> getPlugins​(Class<T> type)
        Returns all registered instances of plugins with the specified type.

        Returned array is sort by plugins priority.

        Example usage: 

         PluginManager pm = ... // get instance
 ResourceDAO[] daos = pm.getPlugins(ResourceDAO.class);
        Type Parameters:
        T -
        Parameters:
        type - the Class object representing the type of plugins in returned array.
        Returns:
        the array with plugins of given type.

      • getPlugins

        @Nonnull
<T extends Plugin> List<T> getPlugins​(Class<T> type,
                                      @Nullable
                                      String keyword)
        Returns all registered instances of plugins with the specified type and keyword.

        Returned array is sort by plugins' priority and contains plugins registered with specified keyword only. If keyword is null, then all plugins of given type are returned. If keyword is a NO_KEYWORDS string, then all plugins of given type with no keyword are returned.

        Type Parameters:
        T -
        Parameters:
        type - the Class object representing the type of plugins in returned array.
        keyword - a keyword specifying the selection of plugins.
        Returns:
        the array with plugins of specified type and with given keyword.

      • getPlugin

        @Nonnull
<T extends Plugin> T getPlugin​(Class<T> type)
        Returns an instance of preferred plugin implementation of specified type.

        If more implementations of plugin with given type are present, then the one with the highest priority is returned.

        Type Parameters:
        T -
        Parameters:
        type - the Class object representing the type of returned plugin.
        Returns:
        the instance of plugin.

      • getPlugin

        @Nonnull
<T extends Plugin> T getPlugin​(Class<T> type,
                               @Nullable
                               String keyword)
        Returns an instance of preferred plugin implementation of specified type and keyword.

        If more implementations of plugin with given type and keyword are present, then the one with the highest priority is returned.

        Type Parameters:
        T -
        Parameters:
        type - the Class object representing the type of returned plugin.
        keyword - a keyword specifying the selection of plugins.
        Returns:
        the instance of plugin.
